description: Median of the ratio between the sale price and the list price for all homes (e.g. if a home with a list price of $200k sells for $250k, its ratio would be 5:4 or 1.25). This data is calculated by Zillow Real Estate Research (www.zillow.com/research) using their database of 110 million homes.
